Judge Hans Fabricius dismissed the application with costs and said a punitive cost order against Moyane is justified based on his “abusive” behaviour throughout the court proceedings. “The application is dismissed with costs including the costs of two counsel,” he said Fabricius said Moyane’s conduct has been abusive towards President Cyril Ramaphosa and retired judge Robert Nugent who was chairing the Sars commission of inquiry. “It is clear from my judgement that the conduct of the applicant in these proceedings is particularly reprehensible and vexatious and abusive. 